# Documentation Language Context

- All documentation must be written in French (en-en).
- All documentation files must be created and maintained in Markdown format (`.md`).
- In documentation, references to files and sections must use clickable Markdown links.
- This includes README content, Markdown docs, architecture notes, runbooks, ADRs, and inline documentation prose.
- If source material is in another language, translate and publish documentation in French.
- Keep terminology consistent across documents.
